WEBVTT

00:01.171 --> 00:02.851
Previously on "Casual"...

00:02.960 --> 00:04.960
Well, it, uh,
looks like you're being asked

00:04.985 --> 00:06.833
to sell a stake in Snooger

00:06.834 --> 00:09.294
to JME Capital.

00:09.295 --> 00:11.004
Jordan Anderson. Thanks for coming in.

00:11.005 --> 00:14.049
So you, took home the boss' wife.

00:14.050 --> 00:16.050
You can hang around,
watch me fire your employees.

00:16.052 --> 00:18.178
Or you can sign.
They all get to keep their jobs,

00:18.179 --> 00:20.013
and Snooger becomes a line item

00:20.014 --> 00:23.308
on a spreadsheet I glance at
every other quarter.

00:23.309 --> 00:26.687
You didn't, uh, borrow
me and Mae-Yi's road bikes

00:26.688 --> 00:28.272
last Saturday, did you?

00:28.273 --> 00:30.399
I just found out
that my friend has cancer

00:30.400 --> 00:33.318
and it's a little hard for me
to think about bikes right now.

00:33.319 --> 00:34.861
Come on, it's tattoo roulette.

00:34.862 --> 00:36.321
The surprise is half the fun.

00:36.322 --> 00:37.781
Emojis?

00:37.782 --> 00:39.324
They're our emojis.

00:39.325 --> 00:41.285
They're from our first text.

00:41.286 --> 00:44.204
So what, you're not into me anymore?

00:44.205 --> 00:45.497
You know that feeling

00:45.498 --> 00:47.666
when you get someone and they get you?

00:47.667 --> 00:49.126
Yeah.

00:49.127 --> 00:50.544
It's gone.

00:53.548 --> 00:54.923
I made a mistake.

00:54.924 --> 00:56.425
I want you back.

00:56.426 --> 00:58.218
Jesus, Drew.

00:58.219 --> 00:59.511
I'm dying.

00:59.512 --> 01:00.637
Where's Mom?

01:00.638 --> 01:02.055
Your mother has chosen to

01:02.056 --> 01:03.807
recuse herself from the situation.

01:03.808 --> 01:06.518
She finds this whole thing
a bit unpalatable.

01:06.519 --> 01:07.686
So we're supposed to take care of you?

01:07.687 --> 01:09.104
Unpalatable?

01:09.105 --> 01:10.772
I'll be euthanizing myself this evening.

01:10.773 --> 01:12.316
This is really what you want?

01:12.317 --> 01:13.567
It is.

01:15.695 --> 01:16.987
Guys?

01:20.783 --> 01:23.410
You're not really going back
to Drew, are you?

01:23.411 --> 01:25.245
No, I don't think I am.

01:25.246 --> 01:28.315
But it's time for me
to leave this house.

01:31.669 --> 01:34.212
It'd been, I don't know,
three weeks, a month.

01:34.213 --> 01:35.881
And I thought she was doing great.

01:35.882 --> 01:37.257
But then the phone rings...

01:37.258 --> 01:40.510
Two days. That's how long it took.

01:40.511 --> 01:42.596
Two days before the texting started.

01:42.597 --> 01:44.598
I wanted to believe
she could leave the nest,

01:44.599 --> 01:46.600
that she could fly, but...

01:46.601 --> 01:48.185
"Hi. How are you? What's going on?

01:48.186 --> 01:49.644
It's... oh... it rain."

01:49.645 --> 01:51.021
I get it. This is all new for her.

01:51.022 --> 01:52.522
A new house, a new world.

01:52.523 --> 01:53.815
It's like that scene
at the end of "Room."

01:53.816 --> 01:55.776
The smiley face, the winky face,

01:55.777 --> 01:57.486
the laugh-cry, cry-cry, the...

01:57.487 --> 01:59.613
And that neighborhood
is not safe at all.

01:59.614 --> 02:02.282
He's an emotional wheel of fortune.

02:02.283 --> 02:05.285
You know, it's just spinning
and spinning and spinning...

02:05.286 --> 02:08.330
She's crying out for help.
"Save me, save me, save me."

02:08.330 --> 02:09.663
Did I tell you that he's

02:09.664 --> 02:11.375
renting out bedrooms like a brothel?

02:11.376 --> 02:12.376
Well, does he

02:12.377 --> 02:13.835
make money from just the rooms

02:13.836 --> 02:15.837
or does he take a piece of the action?

02:15.838 --> 02:16.838
Brothel-wise?

02:16.839 --> 02:18.215
That's not funny because

02:18.216 --> 02:20.676
he... he could end up
with a serial killer.

02:20.677 --> 02:22.219
And serial killers really like

02:22.220 --> 02:25.972
the whole real apartment experience.

02:25.973 --> 02:28.308
You think I'm overreacting?

02:28.309 --> 02:29.434
Yes.

02:31.688 --> 02:33.397
Where is this fucking German?

02:33.398 --> 02:35.315
Thought their whole thing
was efficiency.

02:35.316 --> 02:36.525
German?

02:38.486 --> 02:39.487
Bye, Leon.

02:41.406 --> 02:44.324
Hans!

02:44.325 --> 02:46.410
Hans.

02:46.411 --> 02:48.620
Hans?

02:48.621 --> 02:49.663
Yes.

02:49.664 --> 02:51.249
How do I look?

02:53.876 --> 02:55.044
For what?

02:59.340 --> 03:01.050
Good night.

03:02.719 --> 03:04.094
Hot tub,

03:04.095 --> 03:05.679
record player, bar,

03:05.680 --> 03:08.515
laundry, kitchen that way.

03:08.516 --> 03:10.183
My room.

03:10.184 --> 03:12.395
Dad's charred remains.

03:14.522 --> 03:16.606
And your choice of bedroom.

03:16.607 --> 03:18.525
Left was my sister's.

03:18.526 --> 03:20.527
Right was my niece's.

03:20.528 --> 03:21.903
You really can't go wrong,
but I'm guessing

03:21.904 --> 03:24.197
less weird shit went down in that one.

03:25.533 --> 03:26.575
This will work.

03:26.576 --> 03:28.493
Great. All right, I gotta run,

03:28.494 --> 03:30.287
but text me if you need anything.

03:30.288 --> 03:32.372
Restaurant recs, bars.

03:32.373 --> 03:34.374
It's important you not
see this as an Airbnb

03:34.375 --> 03:36.918
but as your home away from home.

03:36.919 --> 03:38.503
I will try.

03:38.504 --> 03:40.505
Wunderbar.

03:40.506 --> 03:42.717
Don't forget to sign the guest book.

